{"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Instance Method","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"format"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"format"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"UnsafePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"text":"gchar","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":">!) -> ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","text":"String"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}],"extendedModule":"GLib","role":"symbol","title":"format(format:)","externalID":"s:4GLib16DateTimeProtocolPAAE6formatADSSSgSPys4Int8VGSg_tF::SYNTHESIZED::s:4GLib11DateTimeRefV","symbolKind":"method","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Creates a newly allocated string representing the requested "},{"code":"format","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTimeRef\/format(format:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"format","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"format"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"UnsafePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar"},{"kind":"text","text":">!) -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","text":"String","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"!","kind":"text"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The format strings understood by this function are a subset of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"strftime()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" format language as specified by C99.  The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"D"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"U","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"W","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"conversions are not supported, nor is the ","type":"text"},{"code":"E","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" modifier.  The GNU"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"extensions "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"k"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"l","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"s"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"P"},{"type":"text","text":" are supported, however, as are the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"0","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"_","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"-","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" modifiers. The Python extension ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"f"},{"type":"text","text":" is also supported."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"In contrast to ","type":"text"},{"code":"strftime()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", this function always produces a UTF-8"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"string, regardless of the current locale.  Note that the rendering of","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"many formats is locale-dependent and may not match the "},{"code":"strftime()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"output exactly."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The following format specifiers are supported:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"a","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": the abbreviated weekday name according to the current locale","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"A","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": the full weekday name according to the current locale","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"b","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": the abbreviated month name according to the current locale","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"B"},{"text":": the full month name according to the current locale","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"c"},{"type":"text","text":": the preferred date and time representation for the current locale"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"C","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": the century number (year\/100) as a 2-digit integer (00-99)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"d"},{"type":"text","text":": the day of the month as a decimal number (range 01 to 31)"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/e-3m6a4"},{"type":"text","text":": the day of the month as a decimal number (range 1 to 31);"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"single digits are preceded by a figure space (U+2007)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"F"},{"type":"text","text":": equivalent to "},{"code":"Y-","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"m-"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"d"},{"type":"text","text":" (the ISO 8601 date format)"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g"},{"type":"text","text":": the last two digits of the ISO 8601 week-based year as a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"decimal number (00-99). This works well with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"V"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"u"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"G","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": the ISO 8601 week-based year as a decimal number. This works","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"well with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"V"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"u"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"h"},{"text":": equivalent to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"b"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"H","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the hour as a decimal number using a 24-hour clock (range 00 to 23)"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"I","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the hour as a decimal number using a 12-hour clock (range 01 to 12)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"j"},{"text":": the day of the year as a decimal number (range 001 to 366)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"k"},{"type":"text","text":": the hour (24-hour clock) as a decimal number (range 0 to 23);"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"single digits are preceded by a figure space (U+2007)"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"l","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the hour (12-hour clock) as a decimal number (range 1 to 12);"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"single digits are preceded by a figure space (U+2007)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"m"},{"text":": the month as a decimal number (range 01 to 12)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"M","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the minute as a decimal number (range 00 to 59)"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"f"},{"type":"text","text":": the microsecond as a decimal number (range 000000 to 999999)"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"p"},{"text":": either ‘AM’ or ‘PM’ according to the given time value, or the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"corresponding  strings for the current locale.  Noon is treated as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"‘PM’ and midnight as ‘AM’. Use of this format specifier is discouraged, as","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"many locales have no concept of AM\/PM formatting. Use "},{"code":"c","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"X"},{"text":" instead.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"P"},{"type":"text","text":": like "},{"code":"p","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" but lowercase: ‘am’ or ‘pm’ or a corresponding string for"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the current locale. Use of this format specifier is discouraged, as","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"many locales have no concept of AM\/PM formatting. Use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"c"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"code":"X","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instead."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"r","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the time in a.m. or p.m. notation. Use of this format specifier is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"discouraged, as many locales have no concept of AM\/PM formatting. Use ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"c"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"X"},{"text":" instead.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"R","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the time in 24-hour notation ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"H:"},{"text":"M``)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"s","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the number of seconds since the Epoch, that is, since 1970-01-01"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"00:00:00 UTC"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"S"},{"type":"text","text":": the second as a decimal number (range 00 to 60)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"t"},{"type":"text","text":": a tab character"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"T"},{"type":"text","text":": the time in 24-hour notation with seconds ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"H:"},{"type":"text","text":"M:"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"S"},{"type":"text","text":")"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"u","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the ISO 8601 standard day of the week as a decimal, range 1 to 7,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Monday being 1. This works well with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"V"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"V"},{"text":": the ISO 8601 standard week number of the current year as a decimal","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"number, range 01 to 53, where week 1 is the first week that has at"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"least 4 days in the new year. See "},{"code":"g_date_time_get_week_of_year()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This works well with "},{"code":"G","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"u"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"w","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the day of the week as a decimal, range 0 to 6, Sunday being 0."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"This is not the ISO 8601 standard format — use ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"u"},{"text":" instead.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"x","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the preferred date representation for the current locale without"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the time"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"X","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": the preferred time representation for the current locale without","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the date","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"y"},{"type":"text","text":": the year as a decimal number without the century"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"Y","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the year as a decimal number including the century"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"z"},{"type":"text","text":": the time zone as an offset from UTC ("},{"code":"+hhmm","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":")","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":":z"},{"text":": the time zone as an offset from UTC (","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"+hh:mm"},{"type":"text","text":")."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"This is a gnulib ","type":"text"},{"code":"strftime()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" extension. Since: 2.38","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"::z","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the time zone as an offset from UTC ("},{"code":"+hh:mm:ss","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"). This is a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"gnulib "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"strftime()"},{"text":" extension. Since: 2.38","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":":::z","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": the time zone as an offset from UTC, with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":":"},{"type":"text","text":" to necessary"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"precision (e.g., "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"-04"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"+05:30","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"). This is a gnulib ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"strftime()"},{"type":"text","text":" extension. Since: 2.38"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"Z","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": the time zone or name or abbreviation","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"``````: a literal ```` character","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Some conversion specifications can be modified by preceding the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"conversion specifier by one or more modifier characters.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The following modifiers are supported for many of the numeric","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"conversions:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"O"},{"text":": Use alternative numeric symbols, if the current locale supports those.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"_","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": Pad a numeric result with spaces. This overrides the default padding","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"for the specifier.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"-","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": Do not pad a numeric result. This overrides the default padding"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"for the specifier.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"0"},{"text":": Pad a numeric result with zeros. This overrides the default padding","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"for the specifier.","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The following modifiers are supported for many of the alphabetic conversions:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"^"},{"text":": Use upper case if possible. This is a gnulib ","type":"text"},{"code":"strftime()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" extension."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Since: 2.80","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"#"},{"type":"text","text":": Use opposite case if possible. This is a gnulib "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"strftime()"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"extension. Since: 2.80","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Additionally, when ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"O"},{"type":"text","text":" is used with "},{"code":"B","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"b"},{"type":"text","text":", or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"h"},{"type":"text","text":", it produces the alternative"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"form of a month name. The alternative form should be used when the month"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"name is used without a day number (e.g., standalone). It is required in","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"some languages (Baltic, Slavic, Greek, and more) due to their grammatical"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"rules. For other languages there is no difference. ","type":"text"},{"code":"OB","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is a GNU and BSD","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"strftime()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" extension expected to be added to the future POSIX specification,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Ob"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"Oh","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" are GNU "},{"code":"strftime()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" extensions. Since: 2.56","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Since GLib 2.80, when ","type":"text"},{"code":"E","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is used with ","type":"text"},{"code":"c","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"C"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"x","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"X"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"y","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Y"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the date is formatted using an alternate era representation specific to the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"locale. This is typically used for the Thai solar calendar or Japanese era"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"names, for example.","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Ec"},{"type":"text","text":": the preferred date and time representation for the current locale,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"using the alternate era representation"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"EC"},{"type":"text","text":": the name of the era"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"Ex","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": the preferred date representation for the current locale without","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the time, using the alternate era representation"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"EX","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the preferred time representation for the current locale without"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the date, using the alternate era representation"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Ey"},{"type":"text","text":": the year since the beginning of the era denoted by the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"EC"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"specifier","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"EY"},{"text":": the full alternative year representation","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]}],"sections":[],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/datetimeref\/format(format:)"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTimeRef","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTimeRef\/DateTimeProtocol-Implementations"]]},"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/DateTimeRef/DateTimeProtocol-Implementations":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTimeRef\/DateTimeProtocol-Implementations","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/datetimeref\/datetimeprotocol-implementations","role":"collectionGroup","title":"DateTimeProtocol Implementations","type":"topic","abstract":[]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/DateTimeRef/format(format:)":{"role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Creates a newly allocated string representing the requested "},{"code":"format","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"format","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"format","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","text":"UnsafePointer"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar"},{"text":">!) -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"String","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/datetimeref\/format(format:)","title":"format(format:)","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTimeRef\/format(format:)"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/DateTimeRef":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTimeRef","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"DateTimeRef","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"DateTimeRef","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GDateTime"},{"text":" is a structure that combines a Gregorian date and time","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"into a single structure.","type":"text"}],"title":"DateTimeRef","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/datetimeref","kind":"symbol"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"abstract":[],"kind":"symbol","title":"GLib","role":"collection","url":"\/documentation\/glib","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","type":"topic"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/e-3m6a4":{"abstract":[{"text":"The base of natural logarithms.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"text":"let","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"e","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sd","text":"Double","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"role":"symbol","title":"e","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/e-3m6a4","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/e-3m6a4"}}}